FeedPackage.Description: EFHooks simplifies the task of hooking code into EF Code First's extension points and separates concerns to make it easy to unit test your hooking code.
FeedPackage.Summary: EFHooks simplifies the task of hooking code into EF Code First's extension points and separates concerns to make it easy to unit test your hooking code. This is based on Kevin McKelvin's EFHooks project, but has additional features (added by Visoft), like the ability to use the existing data context within a hook. Metadata validation upon saving is enabled too. The main differences from the source fork is the framework logic is implemented in separate class DbContextHooks that allowed to add hooking functionality to any DbContext successors in easy way.
FeedPackage.Tags: EF EntityFramework Entity Framework Hooks SaveChanges Metadata validation
FeedPackage.Title: LionSoft.EFHooks

FeedPackage.Description:
The BarcodeXpress for .NET SDK includes all functionality needed for detecting, reading and writing more than 30 types of barcodes with speed and accuracy.
This powerful control accurately reads and writes common industry 1D and 2D barcodes, detecting them anywhere on the page, in any orientation. You can build .NET applications that recognize multiple barcodes in pages, up to 1000 pages per minute.
Our barcode SDK is not only fast and accurate, but easy to integrate into your applications. With this NuGet package and our user-friendly API you can add barcode capabilities to your application in minutes.
Our Barcode library API supports most common use-case scenarios, such as: * Detect, read and write 1D and 2D barcodes * Grayscale (8bpp) detection on various 1D barcode types. * Recognize barcodes located anywhere on a page * Read damaged, broken and incorrect barcodes that other SDK engines fail to read * Report confidence values for detected barcodes * Compute the row and column information for 2D barcodes. * Return the error correction level for 2D barcodes. * Set an optional minimum size that barcodes must meet to be recognized * Track the internal states of the QR Code as it is being read at any point in the output stream (e.g., Kanji, Numeric, etc.) * ImagXpress provides pre-processing functionality for image cleanup and modification prior to analysis
Our SDK supports most widely used barcodes including: Aztec, Data Matrix, PDF417, QR Code, Add-2, Add-5, Airline 2 of 5, Australia Post 4-state Code, BCD Matrix, Codabar, Code 128, Code 2 of 5, Code 32, Code 39, Code 39 Extended, Code 93, Code 93 Extended, Data Logic 2 of 5, EAN 128, EAN-13, EAN-8, GS1 DataBar, Industrial 2 of 5, Intelligent Mail, Interleaved 2 of 5, Invert 2 of 5, ITF 14, SCC-14, Matrix 2 of 5, Patch Codes, PostNet Royal Mail, RM4SCC, UCC 128, UPC-A, UPC-E, ISBN and more!
FeedPackage.Tags: barcode recognition sdk toolkit library api code39 code128 upc upc-a upc-e isbn qr qrcode aztec datamatrix pdf417 add-2 add-5 airline2of5 australiapost bcd bcdmatrix codabar code205 code32 code39extended code93 code93extended datalogic2of5 ean128 ean-13 ean13 ean-8 ean8 gs1 gs1databar industrial2of5 intelligentmail interleaved2of5 invert2of5 itf14 scc-14 scc14 matrix2of5 patchcodes postnet royalmail rm4scc ucc128
FeedPackage.Title: Accusoft.BarcodeXpress.Net

FeedPackage.Description:
ImageGear for .NET adds enterprise-class image and document viewing, compression, image processing and editing functions easily to any application, with support for PDF, Office documents, more than 100 other file formats and expanded functionality such as optical character recognition (OCR), barcode recognition, and support for medical DICOM images.
ImageGear provides software developers access to the following technologies:
* Edit, convert and compress over 100 image, graphic, and document formats, including raster and vector images, PDF, JPEG, JPEG 2000, GIF, TIFF, DICOM, CAD, ABIC Check Imaging, HD Photo, Camera RAW, and more.
* Image viewing and display with powerful viewing-enhancement functions that take full advantage of Windows GUI features. It includes support for WinForms, WPF, and ASP.NET, and also includes GUI features such as common dialogs for image loading, saving, processing, and more.
* Manipulate and manage PDF and PostScript files (PS, EPS). Our PDF library API supports most common use-case scenarios such as: rasterization, printing, split, merge, annotations, watermarking, text extraction, layers, encryption, optimization, PDF/A validation and conversion, and many more.
* OCR capabilities, including support for over 100 different languages, image pre-processing, zone based processing, and more.
* Barcode support for postal, patch, 1D and 2D barcode recognition and creation
* Printing, TWAIN Scanning, and ability to hook web apps into scanner functions to deliver high-quality scanning directly to cloud storage repositories.
* Advanced image processing capabilities, including hole punch removal, line removal, dotted line removal, noise removal, clean borders, negate, auto-crop, image enhancement, dilation, erosion, despeckle, deskew, rotate, edge detection, segmentation, among many others.
* Annotation capabilities, including the ability to add, edit and burn-in XML-based text and image annotations, stamps and redactions.
FeedPackage.Summary: ImageGear for .NET adds enterprise-class image viewing, compression, image processing and editing functions easily to any application, with support for PDF, more than 100 file formats and expanded functionality such as optical character recognition (OCR), barcode recognition, and support for medical DICOM images.
FeedPackage.Tags: image processing pdf ocr barcode vector office compress optimize scan print annotate computer vision

* The ability to edit, convert, and compress over 100 image, graphic, and document formats, including raster and vector images, PDF, JPEG, JPEG 2000, GIF, TIFF, DICOM, CAD, ABIC Check Imaging, HD Photo, Camera RAW, and more.
* Image viewing and display with powerful viewing-enhancement functions that take full advantage of Windows GUI features. ImageGear includes support for WinForms, WPF, and ASP.NET, and also provides GUI features such as common dialogs for image loading, saving, processing, and more.
* Manipulating and managing PDF and PostScript files (PS, EPS). Our PDF library API supports most common use-case scenarios such as: rasterization, printing, splitting, merging, annotations, watermarking, text extraction, layers, encryption, optimization, PDF/A validation and conversion, and many more.
* OCR capabilities, including support for over 100 different languages, image pre-processing, zone-based processing, and more.
* Barcode support for postal, patch, 1D and 2D barcode recognition and creation.
* Printing, TWAIN scanning, and the ability to hook web apps into scanner functions to deliver high-quality scanning directly to cloud storage repositories.
* Advanced image processing capabilities, including hole punch removal, line removal, dotted line removal, noise removal, clean borders, negate, auto-crop, image enhancement, dilation, erosion, despeckle, deskew, rotate, edge detection, segmentation, among many others.
* Annotation capabilities, including the ability to add, edit, and burn-in XML-based text and image annotations, stamps, and redactions.

FeedPackage.Description:
Includes all functionality needed to work with all Medical DICOM files using a WinForms interface. The Medical API allows you to read, write, display, and annotate medical and DICOM files like dcm, dic, dc3, dicm, jp2, jpc, j2k, j2c, etc.
Our Medical Imaging SDK supports most common use-case scenarios, such as:
* Supports end user’s interaction and WinForms GUI.
* View medical images.
* Perform Multi-Planar Reconstruction (MPR).
* Watermark.
* View, add, and edit annotations.
* Import and export annotations as XML.
* Burn-in annotations.
* Access metadata.
* Print.
* Auto Windows/Level.
* Rescale.
* Invert.
* Apply common image processing algorithms.
* Apply common image viewing operations like zoom, rotate, etc.
* Convert to a variety of document and image types, including raster and vector images, JPEG, JPEG 2000, GIF, TIFF, Microsoft Office formats, DICOM, CAD, ABIC Check Imaging, HD Photo, Camera RAW, and many more.

FeedPackage.Description:
Includes all functionality needed to work with all Medical DICOM files using a WPF interface. The Medical API allows you to read, write, display, and annotate medical and DICOM files like dcm, dic, dc3, dicm, jp2, jpc, j2k, j2c, etc.
Our Medical Imaging SDK supports most common use-case scenarios, such as:
* Supports end user’s interaction and WPF GUI.
* View medical images.
* Perform Multi-Planar Reconstruction (MPR).
* Watermark.
* View, add, and edit annotations.
* Import and export annotations as XML.
* Burn-in annotations.
* Access metadata.
* Print.
* Auto Windows/Level.
* Rescale.
* Invert.
* Apply common image processing algorithms.
* Apply common image viewing operations like zoom, rotate, etc.
* Convert to a variety of document and image types, including raster and vector images, JPEG, JPEG 2000, GIF, TIFF, Microsoft Office formats, DICOM, CAD, ABIC Check Imaging, HD Photo, Camera RAW, and many more.

FeedPackage.Summary: ImageGear.Office package
FeedPackage.Title: Accusoft.ImageGear.Office

FeedPackage.Description:
Includes the functionality to load and display WordprocessingML (Microsoft Word docx files) and SpreadsheetML(Microsoft Excel xlsx files) and Microsoft PowerPoint pptx files. Using this functionality, users can quickly add the ability to render Microsoft Office files, such as a Word file, Excel file, or Powerpoint file, to an image.
ImageGear for .NET also adds enterprise-class image viewing, compression, image processing and editing functions easily to any application, with support for PDF, more than 100 file formats, and expanded functionality such as optical character recognition (OCR), barcode recognition, and support for medical DICOM images.

FeedPackage.Description:
Includes all functionality needed to work with Adobe PDF and PostScript file formats. Read, write, display, and edit PDF, PDF/A, PostScript, EPS, and U3D files. Utilize a comprehensive PDF API built on Adobe® technology. This feature empowers an app to read, modify, and write PDF annotations, bookmarks, and metadata. PDF/A and PDF/X compliance analysis is available.
Our PDF library API supports most common use-case scenarios such as:
* PDF Viewing * Rasterization * PDF conversion from the most popular document and image types, including raster and vector images, JPEG, JPEG 2000, GIF, TIFF, Microsoft Office formats, DICOM, CAD, ABIC Check Imaging, HD Photo, Camera RAW, and many more. * Printing * Splitting and Merging * Annotations * Watermarking * Content editing, text extraction and OCR * Layers * PDF security and encryption * PDF compression and optimization * PDF/A validation and conversion
FeedPackage.Summary: ImageGear includes an extensive PDF library to read, write, display, compress, secure, and edit PDF, PDF/A, PostScript, and EPS. ImageGear also adds enterprise-class image viewing, compression, image processing, and editing functions easily to any application, with support for more than 100 file formats and expanded functionality such as optical character recognition (OCR), barcode recognition, and support for medical DICOM images.
